  schema:name "The Janzen Boys";
  schema:description "The Janzen Boys are a Winnipeg folk/roots family band who started out busking in 2012. Viral internet success led to selling over 10,000 physical copies of their EPs and debut album, |2|, which sparked demand for their first Canadian tour in summer 2024, featuring sold-out shows nationwide. They were awarded both FACTOR (national) and Manitoba Film and Music (provincial) recording grants which has put them back in the studio working with producers, Murray Pulver (Crash Test Dummies, Doc Walker) and Trey Mills (Forrest Blakk).";
