iwts_performer:7500 a schema:Organization;
  schema:name "On The River (Houle, Sewepagaham, Dunn, Ground Zero Productions)";
  schema:description """Debbie Houle and Sherryl Sewepagaham are award-winning artists for their work with Indigenous women’s trio Asani (now retired) winning a 2010 Canadian Folk Music Award and 2006 Juno Nomination for their compositions in Cree and English.

Songwriter Maria Dunn draws deeply on the folk tradition of storytelling through song. Her accolades: 2022 Juno Award (Traditional Roots), 2016 Edmonton Music Prize, 2017 & 2002 Juno nominations.

Videographer Don Bouzek is Artistic Director of Edmonton-based non-profit theatre company Ground Zero Productions.""";
