  schema:name "Duo Cordelia";
  schema:description "Formed in 2016, Duo Cordelia features violinist and composer Vanessa Marcoux and pianist Marie-Christine Poirier. The musicians are very active on the Canadian classical music scene and have collaborated with Debut Atlantic and  BC  Live Performance Network for their 2024 season.  They have received numerous grants from the Montreal, Quebec and Canada Arts Councils and their first collaborative album “Cendres” (2024) recently received an Opus award for album of the year in the category “Ancient, classical, romantic, modern and postmodern”.";
