iwts_performer:7604 a schema:Person;
  schema:name "Jim Burke";
  schema:description """Jim Burke’s voice is gin-soaked, .a pale-faced Louis Armstrong. and a story of the battle for life and dreams.
It wasn’t until later in life that he would be an artist.  For Burke, diagnosed with Leukemia (CLL) that turned acute, he recognized that he had never recorded his songs, 
Burke has recovered and is now using his music to help others with a cancer diagnosis. He has been working with the Alberta Cancer Foundation to raise funds and send a message of hope to other patients.
“Diamonds” is a CD of Jim Burke’s original music.""";
  schema:url <https://vimeo.com/1169019045>;
