  schema:description "É.T.É is a dynamic trio reshaping Québécois trad music with jazz, prog rock, and classical influences. Violinist Élisabeth Moquin, bouzouki player Thierry Clouette, and cellist Élisabeth Giroux craft unique arrangements and original compositions, blending rich harmonies, groove, and electrifying stage presence. Winners of multiple awards, they've toured Canada, the USA, Scotland, Belgium, and Australia. Their latest album, Sur ces eaux, was released in November 2022.";
