iwts_performer:9383 a schema:Person;
  schema:name "Kiiola";
  schema:description """Kiiola is a Toronto-based singer-songwriter, keyboardist, and performer known for her soulful voice and dynamic stage presence.

Originally from Akita, Japan, she blends folk, jazz, and world influences, weaving traditional Japanese folk melodies into her unique sound. A solo artist and member of JUNO Award winner Donné Roberts’ band, she has performed at major events, including singing the Japanese national anthem at Ricoh Woodbine Mile.

Passionate about storytelling, Kiiola brings her songs to life, captivating audiences with every note.""";
