iwts_performer:10087 a schema:Person;
  schema:name "Aysanabee";
  schema:description """Aysanabee (Ace-in-abbey) is an Oji-Cree artist from Northern Ontario who writes anthems for the soul. With a swirling mix of indie, folk, and electronic sounds, and pulse-quickening fingerpicking, his music is hypnotic and melodious. His style compares to Bon Iver, Hozier, and Kings of Leon. 
Aysanabee made history as the first Indigenous artist to win the JUNO Award in the Alternative Album and coveted Songwriter categories (2024). In the last few years, Aysanabee has built a global fan base by performing over 400 shows around the world.""";
  schema:url <https://www.aysanabee.com>;
