iwts_performer:10117 a schema:Person;
  schema:name "REIN";
  schema:description "Laurice Rein Morson is a 17 years old singer songwriter from Langbank, SK. She performed the Oh Canada on Saskatchewan Riders Game at the age of 13, got invited twice after that. She’s  generous of her talent, singing to community events, fundraising, long-term care facilities since she’s 7, and in Telemiracle stage for 7 years. She accompanies herself with playing piano and guitar. Rein released her first single, airplane mode last February 27. She’s writing more songs  to release an album and plans to tour the world to perform her music.";
